text: Walter Woodworth White (December 14, 1862 – July 10, 1952) was a Canadian politician. He served in the Legislative Assembly of New Brunswick as member of the Conservative party representing Saint John City from 1931 to 1935. ==References== Category:1862 births Category:1952 deaths Category:20th-century Canadian politicians Category:People from Saint John, New Brunswick Category:Progressive Conservative Party of New Brunswick MLAs
title: Walter W. White
